# Local Testing Rules

> **Guidelines for testing FeedbackFlow locally**

---

## Pre-Test Checklist

Before running any local tests, **ALWAYS verify both servers are running**:

```bash
# Check frontend (must be port 3006)
curl -s http://localhost:3006 > /dev/null && echo "Frontend ✅" || echo "Frontend ❌"

# Check backend (port 5000)
curl -s http://localhost:5000/api/v1/health && echo "Backend ✅" || echo "Backend ❌"
```

If either server is not running:
- Frontend: `cd frontend && npm run dev`
- Backend: `cd backend && npm run build && npm start`

