## Browser Testing Flow

1. ✅ Verify servers are running (both frontend and backend)
2. ✅ Navigate to the test URL
3. ✅ For OAuth features → ask user to test manually
4. ✅ For other features → test normally with mock login
5. ✅ Clean up test files after testing (don't commit test pages)

---

## Example: Testing a New Feature

```
1. Check servers: curl localhost:3006 && curl localhost:5000/api/v1/health
2. Create test page (if needed)
3. Add route temporarily
4. Navigate and test
5. If OAuth needed → "Please test manually at http://localhost:3006/test/..."
6. Remove test page and route
7. Commit feature code only
```
